      "description": "Offered is a pristine 2006 Mitsubishi Lancer Evolution IX MR, a benchmark of rally-bred performance. This example retains its numbers-matching 4G63 powerplant, featuring MIVEC variable valve timing and a twin-scroll TD05HR turbocharger with zero shaft play. The 6-speed close-ratio manual transmission shifts with clinical precision, delivering power through a fully operational Active Center Differential (ACD). The chassis is factory-stiff, riding on original Bilstein monotube dampers and lightweight forged BBS wheels. Every VIN tag is intact, the undercarriage is free of oxidation, and the valvetrain is silent. A collector-grade specimen with no aftermarket modifications.",
